
<purchabr>ALCAN AUSTRALIA</purchabr> BIDS FOR <acqabr>ALCAN NEW ZEALAND</acqabr>
    SYDNEY, March 27 - <purchaser>Alcan Australia Ltd</purchaser> {<purchcode>AL.S</purchcode>} said it will
make a <dlramt>39.3 mln N.Z. Dlr</dlramt> cash <status>bid</status> for all the issued shares of
{<acquired>Alcan New Zealand Ltd</acquired>} at 1.80 N.Z. Dlrs each with a
four-for-three share alternative.
    Both are 70 pct owned by Canada's Alcan Aluminium Ltd {AL}
which will take the share swap option, <purchabr>Alcan Australia</purchabr> deputy
chairman Jeremy Davis said in a statement. The remainder of
<acqabr>Alcan New Zealand</acqabr>'s totalled issued 21.84 mln shares are
broadly held while <purchabr>Alcan Australia</purchabr>'s are primarily held by
institutions. <acqabr>Alcan NZ</acqabr> last traded at 1.55 NZ dlrs, while <purchabr>Alcan
Australia</purchabr> today ended four cents down at 1.15 dlrs.
    Davis said the offer, which is subject to approval by the
New Zealand Overseas Investment Commission, was a response to
the integration of the two countries' markets under the
Australia-New Zealand Closer Economic Relations treaty.
    Alcan New Zealand shareholders who accept the offer would
also receive the final dividend of 10 cents a share normally
payable on May 27.
    <purchabr>Alcan Australia</purchabr> would invite New Zealand representation to
its board and would apply to list its shares on the New Zealand
Stock exchange, Davis said.
